  "prompt": "How do I know if some one has read my direct message on instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you can tell if someone has read your direct message by looking for the \"Seen\" notification under the message you sent. This is similar to read receipts in other messaging apps. Here\u2019s how you can check:\n\n1. **Open Instagram**: Launch the Instagram app on your smartphone.\n2. **Go to Direct Messages**: Tap the paper airplane icon or the Messenger icon at the top right corner of your home feed to access your DMs.\n3. **Conversation List**: Choose the conversation where you want to check if your message has been read.\n4. **Read Status**: \n   - If the recipient has read your message, you will see the word \"Seen\" or a small profile picture of the recipient at the bottom of your last message.\n   - If they haven\u2019t read it, there will be no indication that the message has been seen.\n\nNote that on Instagram\u2019s Vanish Mode or when messages are sent to individuals who don't follow you, the \"Seen\" notification might not be visible in the same way. Additionally, Instagram allows users to turn off activity status, which might occasionally impact seeing read receipts depending on privacy settings.",
